{"id": "duc04-testb-42:8#24", "contents": "The potential merger would reunite two parts of John D. Rockefeller's Standard Oil Trust, which was broken up by the Supreme Court in 1911. Exxon and Mobil have a history of being fiercely independent, with both companies having already cut back on staff and made themselves lean in order to survive long periods when oil prices are low. However, this has been a particularly unsettling year for the oil industry, and there is little prospect that crude oil prices will recover soon. As a result, chief executives of most oil companies have had to look for suitable partners, with British Petroleum announcing a $48.2 billion agreement to buy Amoco Corp. this summer."}
